"200A":{"department":"CEE","number":"200A","title":"Teaching of Civil and Environmental Engineering","description":"Required of CEE Ph.D. students. Strategies for effective teaching and introduction to engineering pedagogy. Topics: problem solving techniques and learning styles, individual and group instruction, the role of TAs, balancing other demands, grading. Teaching exercises. Register for quarter of teaching assistantship.nn 200A. Aut, 200B. Win, 200C. Spr","min_units":1,"max_units":1,"gers":[],"id":103528,},
"200B":{"department":"CEE","number":"200B","title":"Teaching of Civil and Environmental Engineering","description":"Required of CEE Ph.D. students. Strategies for effective teaching and introduction to engineering pedagogy. Topics: problem solving techniques and learning styles, individual and group instruction, the role of TAs, balancing other demands, grading. Teaching exercises. Register for quarter of teaching assistantship. May be repeated for credit. 200A. Aut, 200B. Win, 200C. Spr","min_units":1,"max_units":1,"gers":[],"id":103529,},
